# Normalize line endings. The generated canonical artifacts are byte-compared
# by --check-canonical, so they must check out identically on every platform —
# Windows' default autocrlf would hand them to the drift check with CRLF and
# fail every fresh clone.
* text=auto
docs/reference/canonical-replacements.json text eol=lf
docs/reference/canonical-replacements.md text eol=lf

# The regression suite (scripts/test-regression.mjs) does a plain string
# comparison of fixture input/output against the committed expected.* files.
# On machines with core.autocrlf=true, a fresh checkout would materialize
# input.* with CRLF while expected.fixed.*/expected.fixall.* stay LF (or vice
# versa), failing the byte comparison for reasons unrelated to the code under
# test. Pin every fixture file to LF regardless of local autocrlf settings.
test/fixtures/** text eol=lf
